- Tue 1 Oct 2019. CMRE (Comite Multisectoriel de la Riposte a la maladie a virus Ebola)
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/2019/10/drc-ebola-cmre-update-october-1.html

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 30 Sep 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 3194, of which 3080 are confirmed and 114 are probable. In total, there were 2136 deaths (2022 confirmed and 114 probable) and 991 people cured;
- 388 suspected cases under investigation;
- 3 new confirmed cases, including: 2 in North Kivu -- 1 in Kalunguta and 1 in Oicha; 1 in Ituri in Mandima;
- 3 new deaths of confirmed cases, including: 1 community death in North Kivu in Kalunguta; 2 ETC deaths -- 1 in North Kivu in Oicha and 1 in Ituri in Mandima;
- no recoveries have been released from ETCs;
- no health workers are among the new confirmed cases. The cumulative number of confirmed/probable cases among health workers is 160 (5% of all confirmed/probable cases), including 41 deaths.

News
9 high-risk contacts from EVD cases from Lwemba in Ituri intercepted in Ngongolyio, North Kivu
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Beni's Ebola virus disease Sub-Coordinator, Dr Pierre-Celeste Adike, announced on Tue 1 Oct 2019 that 9 high-risk contacts of a confirmed cases of #Ebola Virus Disease from Lwemba, a health area of Mandima health zone in Ituri Province with inter-ethnic conflict and insecurity, were intercepted Tue 1 Oct 2019 by the community in the Ngongolyo health area in North Kivu;
- they were intercepted by a neighborhood chief, who automatically alerted the rebel teams at Beni level. A rapid intervention team was dispatched to this place, where the presence of the mayor of the city of Beni was also noted;
- these 9 people were in transit from Beni at the home of one of their family members to Kabasha, Kalunguta, in Butembo's sub-coordination, from their residence in Lwemba, where they went to attend a bereavement. Immediately after this interception, the members of the host family were vaccinated;
- the follow-up of these 9 contacts will continue in Butembo, especially since their names have already been communicated in the coordination of the response;
- as a reminder, for 15 days, the response activities have been suspended in Lwemba following inter-ethnic conflicts and insecurity.

Coordination of the response to the Ebola virus disease epidemic in favour of the supply of consumables provided by economic operators in Mambasa, Ituri
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- The general coordination of the response to the #Ebola virus disease (EVD) has expressed its support for the supply of consumables provided and proposed by economic operators in Mambasa, Ituri province;
- the Vice President of the Economic Federation of Congo (EFC) of Mambasa, Alpha Nasibu Katele, who announced it to the press on [Mon 30 Sep 2019] at the coordination of the Mambasa response after a meeting chaired by the Deputy General Coordinator of the Epidemic Response to Ebola virus disease, Dr Justus Nsio Mbeta, in the presence of the President of the EFC and some members of the EFC Committee in Mambasa, some traders from Mambasa, and partners supporting the response, including WHO, ALIMA, and the Red Cross;
- according to Mr Alpha Nasibu, economic operators in Mambasa are able to supply the base of the response with construction materials, food and would like to see a rotation among traders regarding the rental of large vehicles so that everyone can benefit from the demand for the response;
- this meeting consisted of discussions with economic operators in order to harmonize on the products that the response can buy locally in Mambasa, especially since other needs of the response are international and there are also depots that are already pre-positioned to meet possible eventual needs;
- during this meeting, they were asked to draw up a list of products that could be available in Mambasa to allow the response to exclude them from its list to be ordered from other areas or to inform Mambasa's economic operators of their stock of one or another product;
- indeed, there has already been a 1st meeting between the economic operators of Mambasa and the response teams. During this meeting, economic operators complained that the response team orders their consumables from elsewhere, while in this territory economic operators are ready to respond positively to their needs.

Vaccination
-----------
- A total of 15 days without opening of vaccination rings around 5 confirmed cases in the Lwemba health zone in Mandima [Ituri] due to inter-ethnic conflicts and insecurity;
- no opening of an expanded ring around confirmed cases from 30 Sep 2019 in Biakato health area in Mandima as a result of community reluctance;
- a satellite ring was opened in the Lolwa health area in Mandima.
- Since the start of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 230 956 people have been vaccinated;
- the only vaccine to be used in this outbreak is the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, manufactured by the pharmaceutical group Merck, following approval by the Ethics Committee in its decision of 20 May 2018.

Monitoring at entry points
--------------------------
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the total number of travelers checked (temperature rise) at the sanitary control points is 100 964 142;
- to date, a total of 111 entry points (PoE) and sanitary control points (PoCs) have been set up in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri to protect the country's major cities and prevent the spread of the epidemic in neighboring countries.

--
